snippet.title: Viva Festival  Day 2
snippet.description:
Touchdown! We are back in the scenic Italian town of Locorotondo for our second time at VIVA! Festival – to celebrate, we're doubling our broadcast too.

Following from a worldly worldie on Day 1, Saturday gets even more cerebral. After years of trying, we will finally welcome synth pop genius John Maus to our screens, alongside his full band. This whirlwind of energy will be joined by a broad span of fellow avant-garde talent:

The ever-sharp Laurel Halo will make a welcome return on the decks, alongside Italian sample wizard Nicola Conte and, in a rare turn away from her guitar, Blackest Ever Black's Carla del Forno.

 Live, Bjork endorsed artist K Á R Y Y N will complete a memorable and diverse day as pt.2 of our time at VIVA! Festival 2018.

snippet.title: VIVA Festival
snippet.description:
Touchdown! We are back in the scenic Italian town of Locorotondo for our second time at VIVA! Festival – to celebrate, we're doubling our broadcast too.

Friday perfectly sums up the vital and genre-agnostic state of contemporary dance culture. Goldie will be back on Boiler Room after two years, with a Blue Note special...which is sure to be certifiably very special.

Joining him for a second appearance on BR will be two of our favourite globetrotters in the shape of Awesome Tapes From Africa and Nabihah Iqbal (formerly Throwing Shade).

In the debut camp we have Milanese act STILL, pulling sonically from 1930s Ethiopia and Jamaica, who will be bringing a time-scrambling sound, plus Italian digger duo Rudan.

It makes for a diverse and standout Day 1 of our weekend back with VIVA! Festival.

snippet.title: Fleshback: Queer Raving in Manchester's Twilight Zone Chapter 1-3 | Boiler Room Documentary
snippet.description:
► ‘Fleshback: Queer Raving in Manchester’s Twilight Zone’ is a Boiler Room and British Council film uncovering forgotten stories from Manchester’s queer clubbing scene.

In the 1980s-1990s, Manchester’s queer clubbing scenes was localised around The Hacienda’s seminal queer party, Flesh and a club called Number 1. Aided by hit TV show, Queer as Folk, the city’s gay scene entered the mainstream in the late 90s.

The film explores this history while revealing all about those carrying the torch of alternative rave culture, featuring collectives such as Homo Electric, Meat Free, Body Horror, and High Hoops. Each have a different approach and musical feel, drawing in different crowds, yet sharing the same vision. The film uses archive footage in a way that’s voluntarily anachronistic in places, as a way to highlight the continuum between Flesh and The Hacienda, and the parties that are happening today outside of Manchester’s city centre.

The release of the film marks the 30 years anniversary since Section 28 was enacted. Section 28 was the last piece of homophobic law in the UK, and stated that councils should not "intentionally promote homosexuality or publish material with the intention of promoting homosexuality" in its schools or other areas of their work. Section 28 was enforced in 1988 before it was repealed in Scotland in 2000 and then 2003 in the rest of the UK.

Steffi, DJ and promoter for Meat Free in Manchester says, “People are very honest up North, and big movements don’t always wash with the northerners. We’re not about branding or excluding people. Sexual identity is not at the forefront of our parties.”

Directed by Stephen Isaac-Wilson

snippet.title: A Portrait Of Arthur Russel: Wild Combination | Documentary Trailer
snippet.description:
►Arthur Russell was a farm boy from Oskaloosa who moved to New York (via a Buddhist commune in San Francisco) where he worked and played with artists as fantastically varied as Philip Glass, Allen Ginsberg, Nicky Siano and Richard Hell. A pioneering disco producer, cellist, composer and singer-songwriter, he died aged just 40 in 1992, and is only recently getting the wide, often obsessive, audience he deserves.

Wild Combination is a moving and absorbing portrait of the maverick musician. The film uses rare as well as constructed archival footage and commentary from Russell's family, his partner Tom Lee, his friends and closest collaborators, including Glass and Ginsberg, plus plenty of his brilliant, beautiful dance tracks. Streaming for free on 4:3 from June 3rd 2018.

snippet.title: Queer Raving in Manchester's Twilight Zone | Fleshback: Chapter 1 | Boiler Room Documentary
snippet.description:
► ‘Fleshback: Queer Raving in Manchester’s Twilight Zone’ is a Boiler Room and British Council  film uncovering forgotten stories from Manchester’s queer clubbing scene.

In the 1980s-1990s, Manchester’s queer clubbing scenes was localised around The Hacienda’s seminal queer party, Flesh and a club called Number 1. Aided by hit TV show, Queer as Folk, the city’s gay scene entered the mainstream in the late 90s.

The film explores this history while revealing all about those carrying the torch of alternative rave culture, featuring collectives such as Homo Electric, Meat Free, Body Horror, and High Hoops. Each have a different approach and musical feel, drawing in different crowds, yet sharing the same vision. The film uses archive footage in a way that’s voluntarily anachronistic in places, as a way to highlight the continuum between Flesh and The Hacienda, and the parties that are happening today outside of Manchester’s city centre.

The release of the film marks the 30 years anniversary since Section 28 was enacted. Section 28 was the last piece of homophobic law in the UK, and stated that councils should not "intentionally promote homosexuality or publish material with the intention of promoting homosexuality" in its schools or other areas of their work. Section 28 was enforced in 1988 before it was repealed in Scotland in 2000 and then 2003 in the rest of the UK.

Steffi, DJ and promoter for Meat Free in Manchester says, “People are very honest up North, and big movements don’t always wash with the northerners. We’re not about branding or excluding people. Sexual identity is not at the forefront of our parties.”

Chapter 2 dropping June 5th.
Full documentary series out on June 12th

Directed by Stephen Isaac-Wilson

snippet.title: Dollkraut Feat  Zeid & Maii - Esmak Esmi
snippet.description:
► DL Track Here: http://blrrm.tv/esmak-esmi
► Boiler Room and Ballantine’s True Music partnership returns, taking one step further with the Hybrid Sounds project. Working alongside some of the most engaging live electronic acts in the world, we’ll travel to Moscow, Sao Paulo, Beirut and Valencia, on a journey that will explore the links between acoustic and electronic music, uncovering what can occur when these two distinct styles collide.

On each city visited, the artists collaborate on new original material for our next True Music EP — a record that catalogues the exceptional sounds captured throughout this project. After an exciting collaboration by British duo Overmono with Russian saxophonist Solo Operator, we brought Dutch producer Dollkraut to Lebanon where he worked with Maii and Zeid, a duo formed by legendary Beirut producer Zeid Hamdan and vocalist Maii Waleed.

The final creation, “Esmak Esmi” is the result of Maii’s tranquil lyricism fused with Zeid and Dollkraut’s perfected arrangement and improvisation. The three unique artists, all strongly connected by a shared love for historic instruments and sounds, met in Beirut to create the collaboration track in three days of studio sessions.

snippet.title: Overmono feat. Solo Operator - Foggy Albion
snippet.description:

► Boiler Room and Ballantine’s True Music partnership returns, taking one step further with the Hybrid Sounds project. Working alongside some of the most engaging live electronic acts in the world, we’ll travel to Moscow, Sao Paulo, Beirut and Valencia, on a journey that will explore the links between acoustic and electronic music, uncovering what can occur when these two distinct styles collide.

On each city visited, the artists collaborate on new original material for our next True Music EP — a record that catalogues the exciting sounds captured throughout this project. First up is Moscow, where Overmono, comprised of brothers Truss and Tessela, collaborated with Russian saxophonist, Solo Operator. 

The final production, “Foggy Albion,” sees the acoustic tones of Solo Operator’s saxophone dessicated and immersed in a haunting ambient hinterland crafted by Overmono. The six-minute track further expands on the sonic universe Overmono have explored on their output thus far.

“Sacha completely changed my perception of how a  saxophone can be played, it was inspiring working with someone so dedicated to their music”, Overmono’s Truss reveals on what appealed about the Hybrid Sounds project.

snippet.title: TEASER: The Sound Of Belgium (Documentary) | Coming Sun 18th Feb
snippet.description:
The Sound of Belgium film explores the rich but untold story of Belgian dance music. From the dance halls with Decap organs to the golden days of Popcorn; from EBM and New Beat to Belgian house and techno.

►Streaming for free on Boiler Room TV now: http://blrrm.tv/TSOB  

►At the end of the 80s, Belgium was taken by surprise by the New Beat, a once immensely popular, almost surreal type of dance music. Its unexpected but short lived success didn’t only leave a mark on a new generation of musicians in Belgium in the years to come; its eclectic mix of sounds and styles actually had its seeds in earlier decades.

A story that has been widely ignored by ‘serious’ music critics and the mainstream media in general, 'The Sound of Belgium' goes in search of the spirit of a nation and the people that danced to it.

snippet.title: DJ Harvey re-soundtracks lost tapes from legendary Paradise Garage closing party 1987
snippet.description:
► More here: http://blrrm.tv/final-night-in-paradise
► We're absolutely thrilled to present unseen video tapes from the mythic Paradise Garage's closing party in 1987, re-soundtracked by living legend DJ Harvey.

snippet.title: The Final Night in Paradise - DJ Harvey - A/V Teaser
snippet.description:
►Installation details: http://blrrm.tv/paradise-av ► RSVP for the Party: http://blrrm.tv/paradise-party
►After resurfacing holy grail film Maestro, Boiler Room TV collaborates with DJ Harvey to present an ode to dance music messiah Larry Levan and the church of Paradise Garage with A/V installation 'The Final Night in Paradise.'

Lost video tapes from the mythic Paradise Garage closing party 1987 are presented as a multi-screen television installation with an exclusive, era-evoking soundtrack by living legend DJ Harvey.

The piece mirrors CCTV split-screen monitoring to reveal a Boiler Room-esque voyeuristic window into a night at Paradise Garage.

No cameras were allowed at the Garage yet the installation features never-before-seen original footage of the legendary NYC night club, a rare visual document of clubbing's zenith.

Included are shots of cultural icon Keith Haring`s Pop Art murals and footage of Haring himself dancing during the closing weekend; as well as the maestro Levan spinning to his devoted crowd, and guest performances from diva singers Gwen Guthrie and Liz Torres and a young ESG.

The installation runs from 24-26th November, running 12-6pm daily at The Gallery, an old Victorian brothel in East London. Admission is free.

We'll also be throwing our own final night to the Final Night in the shape of a classic Boiler Room broadcast party, at Village Underground on Sunday 26th. 

Three of the finest disciples of the era join us: Jamie 3:26, DJ Nick the Record and Lucky Cloud / Classic Album Sundays's Colleen 'Cosmo' Murphy, all making their BR debuts. It'll be the penultimate big show of the year for us in London, not one to miss miss out.

snippet.title: Baile Funk São Paulo - an introduction by Boiler Room and Kondzilla
snippet.description:
► Download: http://blrrm.tv/br_App ► More here: http://blrrm.tv/Baile-funk
► Over the last few years, youth in São Paulo have reinvented funk, a musical form born decades ago in Rio’s favelas, and this new incarnation is flirting with mainstream success. The beats have gotten people moving worldwide, but the controversial lyrics and the music’s context are often little understood outside the poor outskirts of South America’s largest city.

Back in 2015, we asked KondZilla – a hugely talented and hugely influential music video director in Brazil’s funk scene – to tell the story of São Paulo funk. In this film – originally a Dailymotion exclusive – Kondzilla came along with us to talk with the MCs, producers and young fans making it all happen.

snippet.title: Musically Mad - UK Soundsystem Documentary - Trailer | Boiler Room
snippet.description:
► Download app: http://blrrm.tv/br_App ► More Here: http://blrrm.tv/musicallymad
► Official Online Premiere: 24 August 2017
To mark the 51st edition of Notting Hill Carnival, Boiler Room TV resurfaces this wicked sound system documentary.

Musically Mad takes you into the hearts and heads of the singers and soundmen, the backbone of the UK roots reggae sound systems. With them they bring the deepest bass and the highest chants, delivered by massive stacks of speakers and custom-built sound equipment. For some, attending a sound system dance is a religious experience, channelled through the music and the message. For others, it’s the natural way to connect with the music they love. Either way, sound system culture is growing and changing.

From their humble beginnings in the backyards of Kingston, Jamaica, sound systems were brought along by Caribbean immigrants, gradually gaining a strong following in the UK. As David Katz included extensive essay “Steel Horns And Bass Bins In Blighty” concludes, the dances were crucial in lifting the spirits of the Caribbean exiles, helping them to forget their hardships. Something that reggae and sound system culture now does worldwide, regardless of colour or nationality.

Musically Mad is the story of the people pushing reggae to the masses, featuring interviews with Iration Steppas, Dougie Conscious Sounds, Ironworks Dread, Terry Gad, Ras Muffett, DJ Stryda, Murray Man, Mikey Dread from Channel One sound, Mad Professor, his son Joe Ariwa, Jah Shaka’s son Young Warrior and many more.

snippet.title: Nina Kraviz & Powell on "Sähkö The Movie" - starring Mika Vainio - Trailer | Boiler Room
snippet.description:
► Stay tuned here: http://blrrm.tv/Sahko
► World Online Premiere: 10 August 2017
Exclusive to Boiler Room TV

Mika Vainio’s death in April 2017 sent shock waves rippling through the electronic music community. The late Finnish musician left an indelible mark on noise thanks to his roles in the ‘90s group Pan Sonic and record label Sähkö Recordings. Over the years, Vainio collaborated with Björk, Suicide’s Alan Vega, drone icon Stephen O’Malley and more. 

Now, just months following his passing, Boiler Room has unearthed a mythic film about the Sähkö label. Artfully shot on 16mm by Jimi Tenor, Sähkö The Movie - a title fans have given the film in the absence of any official one - is a suitably abstract portrayal of the singular label in its prime. Finnish artists featured include Sähkö co-founder Tommi Grönlund, Mono Junk, Hertsi, IFÖ, and, of course, Mika Vainio himself.
 
The film tracks the Finnish unit at work in the studio making tracks on their trademark custom-built analogue equipment, hand-pressing limited edition vinyl releases and their eardrum rupturing yet delicate live performances.
 
Outside of a few select festival screenings and those who own a rare VHS edition released by Blast First Petite, hardly anyone has seen the 44-minute film but this hasn’t stopped it attaining legendary status. Essential viewing for anyone with a passing interest in techno, industrial and experimental music underpinned by a restless DIY spirit. From 10 August 2017, watch the film online for the first time exclusively via Boiler Room TV.

snippet.title: 'Space For Everyone' - a film by Boiler Room, English National Ballet and V&A Museum
snippet.description:
► Download audio: http://blrrm.tv/br_App ► More here : http://blrrm.tv/SpaceForEveryone
► A brand new 5-minute work we (Boiler Room) have made in collaboration with English National Ballet and the Victoria & Albert Museum. All original music created by Overmono.

Directed by our own Martina Piazza, the video features sublime sequential shots following two dancers as they explore the empty spaces within the V&A.

Shot overnight in the museum, the video features English National Ballet dancers Connie Vowles and William Beagley, with choreography by George Williamson. The final film and a live performance of the piece was premiered on Friday 30 June at our Friday Late event with the V&A, which attracted over 6k people to the museum throughout the duration of the evening.

All music is original, created by Overmono - the XL Recordings electronic act comprised of brothers Tessela and Truss.
